            <head>THE RIDDLE</head>
            
            <lg>
               <l>White men’s children spread over the earth—</l>
               <l>A rainbow suspending the drawn swords of birth,</l>
               <l>Uniting and blending the races in one</l>
               <l>The world man—cosmopolite—everyman’s son!</l>
            </lg>
            
            <lg>
               <l>He channels the stream of the red blood and blue,</l>
               <l>Behold him! A Triton—the peer of the two;</l>
               <l>Unriddle this riddle of “outside in”</l>
               <l>White men’s children in black men’s skin.</l>
            </lg>
            
     
            
            
            <byline>-Georgia Douglas Johnson</byline>
